      • create

        Token create(int customer,
             java.lang.String token,
             TokenUse use)
      throws DataAccessException
        Inserts a new registration token into the data storage.
        Parameters:
        customer - The customer the token is issued to.
        token - The token to insert.
        use - The usage of the token to create.
        Returns:
        An instance representing the newly inserted token.
        Throws:
        DataAccessException - When a data storage exception occurs while performing the operation.

      • get

        Token get(int id,
          TokenUse use)
   throws DataAccessException
        Returns the registration token with the provided id.
        Parameters:
        id - The id of the registration token to return.
        use - The use of the registration token to return.
        Returns:
        The registration token with the provided id. Returns null in case no registration token with the provided id exists.
        Throws:
        DataAccessException - When a data storage exception occurs while performing the operation.
